label.value: regulation of mast cell chemotaxis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of mast cell chemotaxis. Mast cell chemotaxis is the movement of a mast cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of mast cell chemotaxis

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of mast cell chemotaxis. Mast cell chemotaxis is the movement of a mast cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: negative regulation of mast cell chemotaxis

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of mast cell chemotaxis. Mast cell chemotaxis is the movement of a mast cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: regulation of response to cytokine stimulus

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of a response to cytokine stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of response to cytokine stimulus

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of a response to cytokine stimulus.

label.value: negative regulation of response to cytokine stimulus

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of a response to cytokine stimulus.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in mammary gland duct morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of branching involved in mammary gland duct morphogenesis.

label.value: cell-cell signaling involved in mammary gland development

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another and contributes to the progression of the mammary gland, from its initial state to the mature structure.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: positive regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: negative regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of mesenchymal cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: regulation of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in tissue homeostasis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation resulting in the maintenance of a steady-state number of cells within a tissue.

label.value: regulation of apoptosis involved in tissue homeostasis

value.value: Any process that modulates the occurrence or rate of cell death by apoptosis that results in the maintenance of the steady-state number of cells within a tissue.

label.value: regulation of cell differentiation involved in tissue homeostasis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell differentiation that contributes to the maintenance of a steady state of a cell type within a tissue.

label.value: ectodermal placode formation

value.value: The developmental process in which an ectodermal placode forms. An ectodermal placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that is the primordium of many structures derived from the ectoderm.

label.value: hair follicle placode formation

value.value: The developmental process in which a hair placode forms. An hair follicle placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the hair follicle bud.

label.value: tooth placode formation

value.value: The developmental process in which the tooth placode forms. A tooth placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the tooth bud.

label.value: sebaceous gland placode formation

value.value: The developmental process in which a sebaceous gland placode forms. A sebaceous gland placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the sebaceous gland bud.

label.value: sweat gland development

value.value: The progression of the sweat gland over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Sweat glands secrete an aqueous solution that is used in thermoregulation.

label.value: sweat gland placode formation

value.value: The developmental process in which the sweat gland placode forms. An sweat gland placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the sweat gland bud.

label.value: cell fate commitment involved in formation of primary germ layer

value.value: The commitment of cells to specific cell fates of the endoderm, ectoderm, or mesoderm as a part of gastrulation.

label.value: regulation of cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of cell differentiation that contributes to the progression of the placenta over time, from its initial condition to its mature state.

label.value: negative regulation of cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of cell differentiation that contributes to the progression of the placenta over time, from its initial condition to its mature state.

label.value: regulation of translation involved in anterior/posterior axis specification

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of translation of mRNAs that contribute to the specification of the anterior/posterior axis.

label.value: lymphatic endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a venous blood vessel endothelial cell acquires specialized features of a lymphatic vessel endothelial cell, a thin flattened cell that lines the inside surfaces of lymph vessels.

label.value: blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a blood vessel endothelial cell, a thin flattened cell that lines the inside surfaces of blood vessels.

label.value: artery development

value.value: The progression of the artery over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. An artery is a blood vessel that carries blood away from the heart to a capillary bed.

label.value: venous blood vessel development

value.value: The progression of the venous blood vessel over time from its initial formation to the mature structure. Venous blood vessels carry blood back to the heart after the capillary bed.

label.value: arterial endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized endothelial cell acquires specialized features of an arterial endothelial cell, a thin flattened cell that lines the inside surfaces of arteries.

label.value: venous endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized endothelial cell acquires specialized features of a venous endothelial cell, a thin flattened cell that lines the inside surfaces of veins.

label.value: branching involved in lymph vessel morphogenesis

value.value: The process of the coordinated growth and sprouting of lymph vessels giving rise to the organized lymphatic system.

label.value: semicircular canal development

value.value: The progression of the semicircular canal from its initial formation to the mature structure.

label.value: semicircular canal formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the semicircular canal from the otic vesicle. This process begins with the regionalization of the vesicle that specifies the area where the vesicles will form and continues through the process of fusion which forms the initial tubes.

label.value: regionalization involved in semicircular canal formation

value.value: The pattern specification process that results in the subdivision of the otic epithelium in space to define an area or volume in which cells will differentiate to give rise to the semicircular canals.

label.value: pouch outgrowth involved in semicircular canal formation

value.value: The morphogenetic process in which an epithelial sheet bends along a linear axis and gives rise to a pouch that will form a semicircular canal.

label.value: limb epidermis development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the epidermis of the limb over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The limb epidermis is the outer epithelial layer of the limb, it is a complex stratified squamous epithelium.

label.value: neural plate pattern specification

value.value: The developmental process that results in the creation of defined areas or spaces within the neural plate to which cells respond and eventually are instructed to differentiate.

label.value: neural plate regionalization

value.value: The pattern specification process that results in the subdivision of an axis or axes of the neural plate in space to define an area or volume in which specific patterns of cell differentiation will take place or in which cells interpret a specific environment.

label.value: embryonic camera-type eye formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a camera-type eye from unspecified neurectoderm. This process begins with the differentiation of cells that form the optic field and ends when the optic cup has attained its shape.

label.value: positive regulation of macrophage cytokine production

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of macrophage cytokine production. Macrophage cytokine production is the appearance of a chemokine due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: heart formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the heart from unspecified parts. This process begins with the specific processes that contribute to the appearance of the heart field and the arrival of cardiac neural crest to the heart region. The process ends when the structural rudiment is recognizable.

label.value: mesenchymal cell differentiation involved in lung development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a mesenchymal cell of the lung. A mesenchymal cell is a loosely associated cell that is part of the connective tissue in an organism. Mesenchymal cells give rise to more mature connective tissue cell types.

label.value: mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in lung development

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a mesenchymal cell population that contributes to the progression of the lung over time. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label.value: cardiac pacemaker cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a pacemaker cell. Pacemaker cells are specialized cardiomyocytes that are responsible for regulating the timing of heart contractions.

label.value: sinoatrial node cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a sinoatrial (SA) node cell. SA node cells are pacemaker cells that are found in the sinoatrial node.

label.value: atrioventricular node cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an atrioventricular (AV) node cell. AV node cells are pacemaker cells that are found in the atrioventricular node.

label.value: cardiac pacemaker cell development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a pacemaker cell over time, from its formation to the mature state. Pacemaker cells are specialized cardiomyocytes that are responsible for regulating the timing of heart contractions.
